                        <ln>Frazier</ln>
                        <fn>James A.</fn>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Mr. James A. Frazier's house at Jennings' Gap and all its contents
                    destroyed by fire on 10/13/1857. Another house of his was also destroyed by fire
                    the previous year.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Convention of Suspended Banks</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Tams</ln>
                        <pf>W.H.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Bank officers from various banks, including Harrisonburg, Wheeling, and
                    Staunton, met in Charlottesville on 10/7/1857, with W.H. Tams of Staunton acting
                    as secretary. Group drafts resolutions calling for maintenance of credit in
                    state banks and various specie regulations; also acknowledging prudence of
                    specie suspension.</summary>
            </div>
