                <summary>Congregation of Presbeterian Church met in Stanton on 10/5/1857 following
                    decision by church pastor, Rev. Joseph R. Wilson, to seek dissolution of
                    appointment. Committee of J.A. Waddell, Wm. A. Bell, and J.D. Rabodan drafted a
                    resolution approving separation and praising Wilson</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Discusses banks and state financial matters. Bottom of page has occasional
                smudges and blurry sections. Discusses Kansas elections. Announces sale of six
                slaves.</pageNote>
